<TITLE> ACC charges Monju, wife over illegal assets </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 7 (bdnews24.com)  The Anticorruption Commission Sunday charged former minister Anwar Hossain Monju and wife Tasmima Hossain with having property holdings inconsistent with their stated income. ACC assistant director Sheikh Fayyaz Alam filed a case with Dhanmondi Police Station, alleging that they had more than Tk 17 crore in unaccounted-for assets. The graft watchdog alleged that Monju and his wife, at various times, illegally amassed wealth worth Tk 17.01 crore. They were also charged with failing to declare about Tk 4.22 crore in the wealth statement they had submitted to the ACC. Monju recently resigned as chairman of a faction of the Jatiya Party. After the state of emergency clamped, he issued a statement that he was retiring from politics and went abroad. His wife, former lawmaker Tasmima, is the editor of the fortnightly "Anannya". bdnews24.com
